verbose_text: In addition, visfatin enables proliferating human endothelial cells to resist the oxidative stress indcued by high glucose, and to productively utilize excess glucose to support replicative longevity and angiogenic activity via SIRT1, while it also induces angiogenesis via the MAPK and PI3K / Akt signaling pathways.
